President Muhammadu Buhari has postponed his visit to Zamfara State. Zamfara State governor, Bello Mattawale, who explained that the development was occasioned by poor weather conditions which affected his flight to the State, however assured that a new date for the President’s visit would be announced later.  The president had soon after, through his media aide, Femi Adesina, sent a video and radio broadcast to the people of the State, in which he stated that he was directing security agencies to sustain the onslaught against terrorists, restrict cross-boundary infiltration and all unauthorised access to the goldmines in the state. The President was scheduled to visit Zamfara state on Thursday 27th January 2022 on a condolence visit over the recent killings in Anka and Bukkuyum local government areas of the State.   President Buhari nonetheless on Thursday commissioned the three millionmetric tonnes per annum cement plant by manufacturing company, BUA Group, and a 48 Megawatts power plant, during a visit to Sokoto State. The President had thanked the Founder of BUA Cement, Abdul Samad Rabiu, and his entire team for their great work in supporting the government’s economic diversification and job creation agenda.